    "title": "Edwards' Tablebases",
    "pageid": 4458,
    "redirects": [],
    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Knowledge\" title=\"Knowledge\">Knowledge</a> * <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">Endgame Tablebases</a> * Edwards' Tablebases</b>\n</p><p><b>Edwards' Tablebases</b>,<br />\nare three-, four and some five-piece tablebases constructed by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven Edwards</a> in the early 90s, initially for his chess program <a href=\"/Spector\" title=\"Spector\">Spector</a>. Edwards' Tablebases rely on <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases#DTM\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">Depth to Mate</a> and the complete coverage for both sides, using one <a href=\"/Byte\" title=\"Byte\">byte</a> per <a href=\"/Chess_Position\" title=\"Chess Position\">position</a>, with evaluations of the forms \"mate in N\", \"lose (get mated) in N\", \"draw\", and \"illegal\". Values for the number N (measured in fullmoves, not <a href=\"/Ply\" title=\"Ply\">ply</a>) for mates range from mate in 1 upto mate in 126 and for losses in 0 (lose in 0 means <a href=\"/Checkmate\" title=\"Checkmate\">checkmated</a>) to lose in 125 moves.  Each file is for a given class (e.g., KBNK) and for a given <a href=\"/Side_to_move\" title=\"Side to move\">side to move</a> (e.g., White) <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>. After finishing the construction procedure in 1994, Steven Edwards made the whole data, documentation and a test program written in <a href=\"/C\" title=\"C\">ANSI-C</a> publicly available on the Internet. Until the advent of the compressed <a href=\"/Nalimov_Tablebases\" title=\"Nalimov Tablebases\">Nalimov Tablebases</a>, Edwards' Tablebases were quite popular and used in several chess programs, such as <a href=\"/Crafty\" title=\"Crafty\">Crafty</a>, <a href=\"/Gromit\" title=\"Gromit\">Gromit</a>, and the commercial <a href=\"/MChess\" title=\"MChess\">MChess Pro</a>, to name a few.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Index_Scheme\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Index Scheme</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#1995_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1995 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Downloads\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Downloads</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Index_Scheme\">Index Scheme</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Index Scheme\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>The index scheme for pawn-less endgames exploits the fourfold symmetry of the <a href=\"/Chessboard\" title=\"Chessboard\">chessboard</a> to restrict the last identified piece to the a1-d1-d4 triangle by <a href=\"/Horizontal_Mirroring\" title=\"Horizontal Mirroring\">horizontal</a>, <a href=\"/Vertical_Flipping\" title=\"Vertical Flipping\">vertical</a>, or <a href=\"/Diagonal_Mirroring\" title=\"Diagonal Mirroring\">diagonal reflections</a>, and features vertical symmetry by confining one pawn to the queen-side flank for endgames with one pawn. Other schemes as applied for instance in <a href=\"/Thompson%27s_Databases\" title=\"Thompson&#39;s Databases\">Thompson's Databases</a>, enumerating all legal positions of both kings as combined index and considering pawns can't reside on the first or eighth rank, feature denser index ranges than Edwards' <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Endgame_Bitbases\" title=\"Endgame Bitbases\">Bitbases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Gaviota_Tablebases\" title=\"Gaviota Tablebases\">Gaviota Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Felicity_Tablebases\" title=\"Felicity Tablebases\">Felicity Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Lomonosov_Tablebases\" title=\"Lomonosov Tablebases\">Lomonosov Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Nalimov_Tablebases\" title=\"Nalimov Tablebases\">Nalimov Tablebases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Scorpio_Bitbases\" title=\"Scorpio Bitbases\">Scorpio Bitbases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Thompson%27s_Databases\" title=\"Thompson&#39;s Databases\">Thompson's Databases</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven Edwards</a> and the Editorial Board (<b>1995</b>). <i>An Examination of the Endgame KBNKN</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#18_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 18, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven Edwards</a> (<b>1996</b>). <i>An Examination of the Endgame KBBKN.</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#19_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 19, No. 1</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess/RN3yWuteQQ4/9G7rH4pFVKMJ\">Announcing forced mates: a poll</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven J. Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, July 21, 1994</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess/PZV47lZr2jE/xxZIRd4q4vIJ\">KBBK tablebases: attempt #2</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven J. Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, August 13, 1994</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/comp.archives/XSXGunhIhjM/VsWof-hiBaoJ\">Updated tablebase documentation</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven J. Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, October 14, 1994</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/comp.archives/806Mshtacxc/rBvnTLgJxqUJ\">KPK tablebases now available via ftp</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven J. Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, October 14, 1994</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1995_...\">1995 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 1995 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/alt.chess.ics/E_3_8Z7sPT8/ufKMjWjxM80J\">Re: FICS vs. ICS: No, really, which is better?</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven J. Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">alt.chess.ics</a>, June 01, 1995</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess.computer/8AKVzXG7Efw/ieMDuzaJjY4J\">MCP6 Endgame Tablebase. Thanks mr.Hirsch!</a> by H.Pieters, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, November 11, 1996</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=11493\">Steve Edward's Endgame Tablebase generator is now available for WIN95</a> by <a href=\"/Michael_Byrne\" title=\"Michael Byrne\">Mike Byrne</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 01, 1997</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=14970\">EGTB</a> by <a href=\"/Frank_Phillips\" title=\"Frank Phillips\">Frank Phillips</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 10, 1998</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=18&amp;t=34259\">Tablebases Edwards</a> by RR, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, July 25, 2001</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=53244\">A different tablebase encoding format</a> by <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven Edwards</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 10, 2014</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Downloads\">Downloads</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Downloads\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/File:Tbgen.zip\" title=\"File:Tbgen.zip\">File:Tbgen.zip</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/File:Spector.zip\" title=\"File:Spector.zip\">File:Spector.zip</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Edwards%27_Tablebases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=11493\">Steve Edward's Endgame Tablebase generator is now available for WIN95</a> by <a href=\"/Michael_Byrne\" title=\"Michael Byrne\">Mike Byrne</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 01, 1997</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Ernst_A._Heinz\" title=\"Ernst A. Heinz\">Ernst A. Heinz</a> (<b>1999</b>). <i>Endgame Databases and Efficient Index Schemes for Chess.</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#22_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 22, No. 1</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/heinz/ps/edb_index.ps.gz\">ps</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Courtesy <a href=\"/Steven_Edwards\" title=\"Steven Edwards\">Steven Edwards</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301111814\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: 